# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Peer Backend â€“ Local Gitleaks Ignore List
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose:
#   Allow developers to locally ignore specific false positives that appear only
#   in their local commits or branches.
#   This file is respected by both CLI and pre-commit scans.
#
#   Do NOT add real secrets here.
#   If a real secret must remain in the repo (rare, approved case),
#   contact the DevOps or CTO team to add it officially in gitleaks.toml.
#
# Usage:
#   Each line should be one of the following formats:
#     - Commit SHA:   e.g.  abc123def456
#     - File pattern: e.g.  tests/mocks/*
#     - Regex:        e.g.  .*FAKE_API_KEY.*
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Common safe patterns
# Postman test data
tests/postman_collection/*
tests/postman_collections/*
mock_data/
fake_*

# UUIDs and hashes used in logs or fixtures
.*[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[1-5][0-9a-f]{3}-[89ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}.*
.*[A-Fa-f0-9]{32,64}.*

# Safe temporary or sample identifiers
.*(tmp|mock|fixture|sample|placeholder|example)\..*
.*(fake|dummy|sandbox).*token.*

# Generated config or build artifacts
runtime-data/*
storage/*
vendor/*
node_modules/*

# Ignore local test JSONs and migrations
sql_files_for_import/*
tests/data/*
migrations/tmp/*
